      "weather": "fine",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FIVE RINGS (4) came from next to last on the corner to record an impressive win over a similar trip to this on the Gold Coast poly last start. Can race closer from a better draw this time. Has won three from six at this distance and just needs to bring poly form to a heavy turf track to be winning again. HEADSTRONG (6) did some work after an awkward start then dug deep at the other end to record a gutsy win over 1540m at the Gold Coast ploy a fortnight ago. That followed a 32-day break so there is improvement to come. The wet track is the only query. MATAWAI (1) was very good first-up at Ipswich then outclassed over 1680m at the same track more recently. Has a strong third-up profile so watch for a much better run. KAAZI (3) led for home but couldn't keep going over the mile at the Sunshine Coast last Sunday. Will handle this going so keep him in mind. GAVIN (8) returned to form last start which coincided with him finding a heavy track. Must be considered again.",
